JOHANNESBURG – Hip hop artist Cassper Nyovest has been accused of overstating his accomplishments. The Tito Mboweni hitmaker took to social media to boast about his accomplishment of apparently selling 10 million units. South African producer and DJ Maphorisa had none of it and charged Nyovest with lying to his fans. WATCH: Cassper Nyovest drops another hot music video The Midnight Starring muso accused Nyovest of conflating figures, saying he meant 10 million streams. DJ Maphorisa was subsequently blocked for his comment, which he defended saying he “didn't mean it in a negative way”. eNCA